---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { GAME_NAME } from '../data/site';

const pageSourceIds = ['DB-TRENDS-001', 'DB-SERP-001', 'DB-LEAD-001', 'DB-LEAD-002'];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Codes Status"
  description="Demon Born codes status — no official code feed confirmed. How to find active codes safely."
  canonicalUrl="/codes/"
  breadcrumb={[{ label: 'Codes Status', url: '/codes/' }]}
  evidenceNotes="No official code source confirmed — third-party code lists are not copied"
  sourceIds={pageSourceIds}
>
  <h1>{GAME_NAME} Codes — Status</h1>

  <p class="page-lead">
    Are there active {GAME_NAME} codes? Current status: <strong>no official code source has been confirmed</strong>.
    This page explains why and how to check safely.
  </p>

  <div class="info-block" style="border-left-color: var(--color-warning-text); background: var(--color-warning-bg)">
    <strong>No official codes published on this site.</strong>
    Codes appearing on third-party sites (Pocket Tactics, Destructoid, Beebom, Radio Times, etc.)
    are not copied here. No code is published without confirmation from an official Roblox channel
    or verified in-game redemption UI.
  </div>

  <h2>Why no codes are published yet</h2>
  <p>
    Google Trends data (<code>DB-TRENDS-001</code>) shows <em>Demon Born codes</em> as a rising
    related query. Third-party code sites (Pocket Tactics, Destructoid — <code>DB-LEAD-001/002</code>)
    have published code lists. However:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>No official Roblox channel (game page, creator Discord, group description) has been
        confirmed as a code source.</li>
    <li>Codes on third-party sites cannot be verified as active or accurate without
        in-game confirmation.</li>
    <li>Expired or incorrect codes published on aggregators can mislead players.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to find codes safely</h2>
  <p>Until an official code source is confirmed, use these verification steps:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Check the official Roblox game page description for any pinned codes.</li>
    <li>Visit the official SoraExp Roblox group page for announcements.</li>
    <li>Check the Roblox game description in-game at the main menu.</li>
    <li>If a creator Discord is confirmed official, check its announcements channel.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>What this site tracks</h2>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Item</th>
          <th>Status</th>
          <th>Source</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Official code list on Roblox game page</td>
          <td>Not confirmed</td>
          <td>DB-API-001 / DB-ROBLOX-001</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Codes pinned in official Discord</td>
          <td>No official Discord confirmed</td>
          <td>DB-SERP-001</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Codes in official Twitter/X or social media</td>
          <td>Not researched</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>In-game code redemption UI</td>
          <td>Requires hands-on verification</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>How codes will be added</h2>
  <p>
    When an official code source is confirmed (official game page, creator channel, or
    in-game redemption UI), the Codes page will be updated to include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Active codes with rewards and expiration status</li>
    <li>Redemption steps</li>
    <li>Expired codes with last-seen dates</li>
    <li>Verification source for each code</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    All codes will be tied to a <code>claim_id</code> and <code>source_id</code> before publication.
    No codes are added from third-party aggregators.
  </p>

  <h2>Submit an official code source</h2>
  <p>
    If you have verified an official Roblox channel that publishes {GAME_NAME} codes,
    use the <a href="/contact/">correction workflow</a> with the URL.
    Once confirmed, the codes page will be updated.
  </p>
</ContentLayout>